originalText.text:
When I moved to the area two years ago this was the first place I tried and never looked back. Affordable prices and good quality. I just moved out of the neighborhood and am still traveling back down to go for my nails. It’s not a fancy boutique place, but you can’t beat the prices and people!

4/5/23 another visit in back in the neighborhood and another amazing job! Asked for a  marshmallow type color but not too white and she delivered

6/29 very patient as I took forever to choose a color

originalText.text: Very inexpensive for the neighborhood, and they do a great job. Try booking in advance or getting there right after work because it's  a small place. The workers are great and very humble, but I don't think the owner is as nice. The owner can be very rude at times and very controlling with her staff. She could get rough while doing clients' nails, that's why I don't have her take care of my nails. I stopped going due to Annie's behavior towards me and others, including her staff. Too bad because this is the most affordable Nail Salon in Manhattan.

originalText.text: I've read a lot of the reviews and I can see what other customers are saying can happen. They can be rude but never to me. Some people wait longer than others. I've always gone there only for pedicures. They do a great job for the price. One day I decided to get a fill-in with acrylic with gel polish. It appeared to be a great job. 3 weeks later I go back to my regular nail salon and find out that I have 2-3 nails that have fungus. If you regularly use acrylic on your nails, you must go to a nail salon that specializes in this. I still plan on going here for pedicures. They are the best

originalText.text: I love the workers because they really do a good job and are very humble.  The owner, Annie, is another story. She has a tendency to talk to her workers in chinese to change the flow of things and they just follow her demands She is very rude when people call on the phone to make appointments,  I've been in her presence when this has happened, and she makes fun of the people on the phone. If she doesn't like you. It isn't in your best interest to go there because she will make her workers do what she wants, like waiting even though you came before someone else without an appointment. She has done it to me, but I'm patient enough to ignore stuff like that. I go because I like one of  her workers,  and she's been caring for my nails for a long time. It is also the cheapest price you will find in the neighborhood. I am now looking for another nail salon due to the owner Annie's ill attitude and behavior to her customers.
